<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yavlinskiy `Would Agree' To Head Government </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1901113694 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1126 GMT 19 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1901113694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS corespondent Lyudmila Aleksandrova] </F>
  [Text] Moscow January 19 TASS -- Russian economist Grigoriy 
Yavlinskiy said on Wednesday he would agree to head a government 
"oriented to overcome an economic crisis" which he predicted 
would occur in March. 
  Yavlinskiy told reporters that in his government current 
Finance Minister Boris Fedorov would chair the Central Bank, 
while Anatoliy Chubays would remain the privatisation supremo. 
  The leader of the Yabloko parliamentary faction said he had 
not received any offers to join the government of Viktor 
Chernomyrdin, but had there been any he would have "submitted a 
programme of extreme anti-crisis measures in three weeks". 
  However, Yavlinskiy added that he would assume the 
responsibility "only on condition that the president exerts no 
pressure and does not interfere". 
  Yavlinskiy believes that First Deputy Premier Yegor Gaydar 
had resigned because of the economic situation which had sharply 
aggravated of late. 

</TEXT>

