<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Chubays Vows To Carry On With Privatization </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1801211194 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 1900 GMT 
18 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1801211194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Rossii Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Excerpt from interview with Anatoliy Chubays, deputy prime </F>
minister and chairman of the State Committee for State Property, 
by unidentified correspondent; place and date not given -- 
recorded] 
  [Text] [Chubays] It is hard for me to speak about the whole 
government or forecast its destiny. But I can speak for myself 
personally, especially as my mind is made up. I am sure I am 
obliged to bring to completion the job for which I stood for 
election. Privatization will be brought to conclusion and the 
commitments that were made will be fulfilled. 

</TEXT>

