<H3> <TI>   Security Council Discusses Hardware Development </TI></H3>
<H4>   Council Maps Out `Principles' </H4>
<F P=102> LD1901124994 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1222 GMT 19 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1901124994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent] </F>
  [Text] Moscow January 19 TASS -- A meeting of the Russian 
Security Council was held in the Kremlin today under the 
chairmanship of President Boris Yeltsin. In light of the "Basic 
Principles of the Military Doctrine of the Russian Federation", 
the council discussed programmes for developing and producing 
perspective types of armaments and military hardware. 
  The Security Council mapped out the key directions and 
principles on which this work is to be organised. The 
implementation of these programmes will allow Russia to keep the 
combat readiness of its Armed Forces at the necessary and 
sufficient level, to guarantee Russia's dependable security by 
rationally using the country's scientific, technological, 
defence, and industrial potential with the optimal expenditure 
of forces and resources. 
  The president of the Russian Federation issued concrete 
instructions to implement the decisions adopted by the Security 
Council, the press service of the Russian president reported 
today. 

</TEXT>

