Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A meeting of the Russian Security Council, chaired 
by Boris Yeltsin, is today discussing a program for development 
and production of new armaments and military hardware. 
  Observers note that not all the members of the Security 
Council are attending the meeting. Those absent are Defense 
Minister pavel Grachev, Interior Minister Viktor Yerin, as well 
as Yegor Gaydar and Finance Minister Boris Fedorov. 
  Interfax reports that Fedorov arrived for the meeting, but, 
having learned he was not invited, left again. He told 
journalists in an interview that he had not expected such a 
development. 

