<H3> <TI>   Security Council Discusses Hardware Development </TI></H3>
<H4>   Council Procedures Reported </H4>
<F P=102> LD1901124394 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1218 GMT 19 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1901124394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Gennadiy Talalayev] </F>
  [Text] Moscow January 19 TASS -- A regular meeting of the 
Russian Security Council was held in the Kremlin here today 
under the chairmanship of President Boris Yeltsin. 
  The agenda of the meeting, the first this year, included 
only 
one item: "On the programme for developing and producing 
perspective types of armaments and military hardware". 
  Reports on this subject were delivered by Andrey Kokoshin, 
first deputy defence minister of the Russian Federation, Viktor 
Glukhikh, chairman of the Russian State Committee for Defence 
Sectors of Industry, and Viktor Mikhaylov, Russian minister for 
atomic energy. 
  The meeting was attended by Viktor Chernomyrdin, chairman of 
the Russian Government, Oleg Lobov, secretary of the Security 
Council, and other council members. Taking part in the meeting 
also were Oleg Soskovets, first vice-premier, and Yuriy Baturin, 
presidential assistant for national security, who was appointed 
to this post early this January. The latter two, are not 
members of the Security Council. 
  Absent from the meeting were such members of the Security 
Council as Defence Minister Pavel Grachev, Interior Minister 
Viktor Yerin, and also Yegor Gaydar. As to Vice-Premier Boris 
Fedorov, he came to the Kremlin in the morning, but unexpectedly 
left it before the meeting began. 
  A statement on the results of the meeting is expected to be 
released by the presidential press service later in the day. 

</TEXT>

