<H3> <TI>   Security Council Discusses Hardware Development </TI></H3>
<H4>   First Meeting Viewed </H4>
<F P=102> LD1801164294 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1433 GMT 18 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1801164294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Moscow January 18 ITAR-TASS -- The first meeting of 
the Inter-Departmental Commission of the Russian Security 
Council, formed by presidential decree, was held here today. 
  The meeting of the commission, headed by Deputy Interior 
Minister of the Russian Federation Aleksandr Kulikov, has 
discussed problems linked with the elaboration of a public 
security concept. It also endorsed the commission's procedural 
rules and working plan, envisaging the study of such problems as 
political extremism, migration of the population, and Russia's 
hot spots. 
  Taking part in the meeting were representatives of the 
Procurator-General's office, Justice Ministry, Defence Ministry, 
Ministry of Culture, Ministry of Social Protection, Ministry of 
Foreign Affairs, the Federal Migration Service, and other 
federal executive bodies. 
  The public security commission is faced with the task of 
determining the priorities of state policy and drawing up 
proposals for the Russian Security Council on ways to ensure the 
vitally important interests of the Russian society, human 
rights, as well as forecasting events and preparing 
recommendations to prevent inter-ethnic and social conflicts, 
political extremism, and various emergency situations. 

</TEXT>

