<F P=100> Latvia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kozyrev Ideas on Baltics Seen as Threat </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1801221094 Riga Radio Riga Network in Latvian 2000 GMT 18 
Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1801221094 </F>
<F P=104>  Riga Radio Riga Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Latvian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report from press center of the Foreign Ministry of the </F>
Republic of Latvia] 
  [Text] According to reports in the Russian media, at a 
discussion meeting of Russian foreign ministry organizations, 
Foreign Minister Andrey Kozyrev made a speech of a conceptual 
nature touching on relations with the Baltic countries. The 
report expresses ideas that are contrary to Russia's previous 
official position, and which are to be regarded as threats to 
Latvia's sovereignty. The Baltic states, including Latvia, are 
named as a region in which Russia's most important interests are 
concentrated, and from which the greatest danger to Russia's 
interests comes. Thus it is important that Russia should not 
leave, and should not withdraw its troops from these regions. 
  The Foreign Ministry of the Republic of Latvia is analyzing 
the new situation. Latvia will also propose discussing this 
issue at tomorrow's meeting of the three Baltic prime ministers 
in Jurmala. 

</TEXT>

