<F P=100> Lithuania </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ministry Concerned Over Kozyrev's Remarks </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1801210194 Vilnius Radio Vilnius in English 2000 GMT 18 
Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1801210194 </F>
<F P=104>  Vilnius Radio Vilnius </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Lithuanian Foreign Ministry has voiced concern 
about Russia's attitude toward the Baltic states, which it calls 
the near abroad. Lithuania does not agree with such a term and 
is concerned, because Russia is again reproaching for 
infringements on human rights in the Baltic countries, which 
does not correspond to reality, says the Lithuanian Foreign 
Ministry document. 
  Lithuania's reaction followed a statement made by Russian 
Foreign Minister Andrey Kozyrev on Tuesday on Russia's vital 
interest in the CIS countries and the Baltics, which says that 
the Baltic states are the zone of Russia's most important 
interest and Russia need not withdraw its troops from the 
region. 
  The Russian foreign minister also demanded to legalize 
double 
[as heard] citizenship. Only people of the independent 
Lithuania and power structures supported by them can decide what 
way of granting citizenship is to be opted for. And any 
pressure [words indistinct] (?as interference in the Lithuanian 
internal affairs), according to the statement of the Lithuanian 
Foreign Ministry. 
  The document says that Russia apparently has not given up 
its 
military influence in the Baltic states. 

</TEXT>

