<H3> <TI>   Federation Council Approves Creation of 10 Committees </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1401220094 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1911 GMT 14 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1401220094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Federation Council has approved 10 committees 
which to work within the framework of the parliament upper 
house. They include the committee for matters concerning the 
Federation, the federal treaty and regional policy; for 
constitutional legislation and judicial and legal issues; for 
budget, taxation, financial, currency, credit and customs 
regulation; for monetary emission; committees for economic 
reform, ownership and property; for CIS affairs; for 
international affairs; for security and defence; for social 
policies; as well as committees for agrarian policies and for 
science, culture and education. Also created was the temporary 
commission for parliamentary procedure and time limit. 

