<H3> <TI>   Gas Pipeline Heavily Damaged in Explosion </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1201181894 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 1700 GMT 
12 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1201181894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Rossii Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] According to a NeGa agency report, the damage from 
the explosion yesterday on the Georgian section of the pipeline 
providing gas to Armenia is greater than that caused by earlier 
acts of sabotage. Some 800 meters of the main trunk line were 
put out of action, the bridge over the Kura River was destroyed, 
and the back-up pipeline was badly damaged. As is known, as a 
result of the earlier acts of sabotage, no gas has been pumped 
to Armenia since 18 December. Experts believe that it will be a 
month before the gas pipeline is back in service, since the 
approaches to the damaged area have been mined. The Armenian 
side is blaming a subversive group from Azerbaijan for the 
sabotage. 

</TEXT>

