<F P=102>  NC1201183494 Yerevan SNARK in English 1105 GMT 12 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1201183494 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan SNARK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tbilisi, January 12 (SNARK) -- Today the Georgian 
Parliament goes on discussing a statement of Vakhtang Goguadze 
about the necessity of Georgia's entrance to the rouble zone. 
Yesterday parliamentarians and government officials expressed 
their opinion of that. The opposition, including Nodar Natadze, 
the leader of the National Front, considers Georgia's entrance 
to the rouble zone as a loss of independence. 
  Vice-Premier Amiran Kadagishvili in his statement doubted 
that Russia would accept Georgia to the rouble zone. In the 
opinion of the Georgian Finance Minister David Jakobidze, the 
concurrent introduction of the Russian rouble and the Georgian 
coupon is necessary. 
  In the interview to the SNARK reporter Nodar Djavakhishvili 
said that Russia proposes unacceptable terms. He is of the 
opinion that monetary and credit emission is to be cut down, the 
budget deficit should be minimal and crediting has to be stopped. 

</TEXT>

