<F P=100> Georgia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Russia Agrees on Return </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1301132194 Tbilisi IBERIA in Georgian 1115 GMT 13 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1301132194 </F>
<F P=104>  Tbilisi IBERIA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Georgian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tbilisi, 13 Jan -- An Iberia correspondent learned 
that the Russian Government has notified the Georgian 
authorities through unofficial sources that Russia has agreed to 
accept Georgia in the ruble zone provided Georgia agrees to the 
following terms: 
  1. To refuse foreign assets; 
  2. to hand over to Russia goldmines or pawn Georgia's state 
property in an exchange for the amount of imported Russian 
rubles; 
  3. to refuse carrying out its own credit emissions; 
  4. the Russian Government is to confirm the state budget [as 
heard]; 
  5. to annul all economic laws and introduce laws adopted by 
Russia on the territory of Georgia; 
  6. to annul the Georgian customs system and merge it with 
the Russian customs office; 
  7. the Russian Government is to appoint one of the vice 
presidents of the National Bank of Georgia. 

</TEXT>

