<H3> <TI>   Shevardnadze Heads Delegation to Turkey </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1201130594 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1102 GMT 12 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1201130594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A Georgian delegation, led by Eduard Shevardnadze, 
left for an official visit to Turkey on Wednesday. It includes 
the Foreign Minister Aleksandr Chikvaydze, the Interior Minister 
Shote Kvaria, and the Minister for Industry Tenghiz Geleishvili 
[as received]. 
  On the way to Turkey, the plane landed at Batumi, where the 
delegation was joined by Aslan Abashidze, the Chairman of 
Ajaria's Supreme Soviet. 
  Abashidze has told Interfax that he intends to discuss with 
Turkish leaders plans to invest in Ajaria's economy, modernize 
Batumi's docks, and supply electricity to the republic. 
  During the visit, Eduard Shevardnadze is to meet with 
Turkey's President Suleyman Demirel, Prime Minister Tansu 
Ciller, the Parliament's Chairman Husametdin Jindoruk, and the 
opposition leader Mesut Olmaz. 
  The sides are to sign a political declaration on the 
principles of relations and development prospects, a protocol on 
relations between the parliaments of the two countries, 
agreements on custom regulations, on cooperation in economy, 
trade, and agriculture, and separate accords on contacts in 
science and technology, in culture, tourism, and sports. 

</TEXT>

