<F P=100> UKRAINE </F>
<F P=101> International Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Supreme Council Member Meets WEU, NATO Officials </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2001090594 Kiev UNIAR in Ukrainian 2200 GMT 19 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2001090594 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UNIAR </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Ukrainian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Brussels, 19 January -- Issues of European security 
and prospects for Ukraine's cooperation with Western military 
and political organizations were discussed at meetings between 
Vasyl Durdynets, first deputy chairman of the Ukrainian Supreme 
Council, and Willem van Eekelen, secretary general of the 
Western European Union [WEU]. Mr. Durdynets focused the 
attention of his interlocutor on the importance of guaranteeing 
territorial integrity and security of Ukraine as an inalienable 
condition of peace and stability. 
  Issues of Ukraine's integration into the European economic 
processes and the necessity of overcoming as soon as possible of 
Ukrainian artificial isolation from the European and world 
economic space were discussed at a meeting between Vasyl 
Durdynets and the leading members of staff of the European 
Community Commission. 
  Talks with NATO Deputy Secretary General Von Moltke [title 
as 
received], members of the staff of the International 
Secretariat, and representatives of the NATO member states in 
the Political Committee of this organization were dedicated to 
Ukraine's participation in the program "Partnership for Peace" 
and a profound explanation of Ukraine's stand on nuclear 
disarmament issues. 
  Taking part in the meetings were also the leaders of the 
Ukrainian president's service for international issues Anton 
Buteyko and Ukraine's ambassador to Benelux, Vasylenko. 
  This has been reported by the information department of the 
Foreign Ministry of Ukraine. 

</TEXT>

