<H3> <TI>   Agreement With Russia on Use of Space Center </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1801191794 Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service in Ukrainian 
1600 GMT 18 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1801191794 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Ukrainian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Agreement has been reached between Ukraine and 
Russia on jointly using the space flight control center near 
Yevpatoria in the Crimea. This was reported today by Ukraine's 
National Space Agency. 
  The center was set up in 1960 under the leadership of Sergey 
Korolev. It has been out of action for the past year and a half 
because of attempts to divide it between Ukraine and Russia. 

</TEXT>

