<F P=101> International Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Baltin Enlists Yermakov Under Command </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2001143594 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1343 
GMT 20 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2001143594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Roman Zadunayskiy] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 20 Jan--Admiral Eduard Baltin, commander of 
the Black Sea Fleet, signed an order today enlisting Ivan 
Yermakov under his own command. Yermakov had been removed from 
the office of representative of the Ukrainian president in 
Sevastopol. An ITAR-TASS correspondent was told at the 
headquarters of the Black Sea Fleet that the decision coincides 
with the opinion of Yermakov himself, who previously occupied 
the office of head of an aircraft repair plant and has the rank 
of colonel in the Navy. Moreover, he never took the Ukrainian 
oath and did not express any desire to serve in the Ukrainian 
Armed Forces. 
  The commander of the Black Sea Fleet has ordered the head of 
the fleet's personnel department to establish Yermakov in the 
post within two months in keeping with his wishes. 

</TEXT>

