<F P=100> UKRAINE </F>
<F P=101> International Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Rukh Leader Criticizes Kravchuk, U.S. </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1901222994 Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service in Ukrainian 
1700 GMT 19 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1901222994 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Ukrainian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Ukraine's president did not betray anything because 
one cannot betray something he did not dedicate himself to. Les 
Tanyuk, member of the presidium of the Supreme Council of 
Ukraine and of the central leadership of the Ukrainian People's 
Movement for Perestroyka [Rukh], said this to a RUKH-PRESS 
correspondent. The act committed by Leonid Kravchuk on 14 
January in Moscow did not give any advantages whatsoever to 
Ukraine, either in the political or the economic spheres, Les 
Tanyuk is convinced. By signing the Russian-U.S. categorical 
demands, Kravchuk proved that he can only be a sprinter but not 
a long-distance runner in world politics. Les Tanyuk also 
believes that the absence of the mechanisms of eliminating 
nuclear weapons in the signed trilateral statement deprives 
Ukraine of any guarantees of its own security. 
  The Rukh leader stressed that the United States has again 
made a drastic mistake, as far as Russia is concerned. Even the 
outcome of the latest election did not cause the United States 
to refrain from supporting the imperial policy conducted by 
Moscow which, following the czarist and communist regimes, is 
now being revived under the banner of Zhyrynovshchyna [code of 
ideas and norms of behavior associated with Zhirinovskiy]. All 
this reminds Les Tanyuk of the events connected with the 
official recognition of the USSR by Washington in 1933, 
precisely when the famine in Ukraine, engineered by Moscow, was 
at its peak. By such dangerous actions the West is forging 
nails for its own crucifixion by Russian national chauvinism, 
Les Tanyuk emphasized. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

