<F P=100> UKRAINE </F>
<F P=101> International Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Green Party Favors Accord With Reservations </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2001183594 Kiev UNIAN in Ukrainian 1406 GMT 20 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2001183594 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UNIAN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Ukrainian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A session of the Green Party of Ukraine took place 
on 20 January apropos the signing of the tripartite statement by 
the presidents of the United States, Ukraine, and Russia on 
eliminating nuclear weapons in Ukraine. In particular Vitaliy 
Kononov, chairman of the party, and Sergey Kurykin, chairman of 
its political council, took part in the session. The "greens" 
evaluated favorably the document, which had been signed. "The 
agreement gives a new impulse to making external ties more 
vigorous and strengthening them, which in its turn will 
stimulate potential foreign investors to become more active, 
Vitaliy Kononov noted. The reservation lies in the fact that 
compensation for nuclear weapons in the shape of fuel for 
operational Ukrainian atomic electric power station is not 
grounds for their further development." 
  The concern of the Green Party of Ukraine is evoked by the 
conditions for processing and burying radioactive waste. 
  Regarding the proposal of the Kharkov "greens" to nominate 
Leonid Kravchuk for the Nobel Peace Prize for steps toward the 
non-nuclear status of Ukraine, Kononov replied that the Green 
Party of Ukraine is still going to examine this issue, because 
at present they do not have information about the mechanism for 
granting this prize. 

</TEXT>

