<H3> <TI>   Military Cooperation Accord Signed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2001144994 Kiev UNIAR in Ukrainian 1232 GMT 20 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2001144994 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UNIAR </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Ukrainian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Kiev, 20 January -- An official meeting between the 
defense ministers of Ukraine and the Republic of Uzbekistan was 
held at the Ukrainian Defense Ministry. Agreement on this 
meeting had been reached during the Ukrainian president's stay 
in Ashgabat at the end of last year. As early as in 1992 the 
two countries' military departments concluded the Agreement on 
Cooperation. Today Uzbek Defense Minister Lieutenant General 
Rustam Akhmedov and Ukrainian Defense Minister Army General 
Vitaliy Radetskyy signed the bilateral Agreement on Military 
Cooperation. The participants in the meeting expressed 
certainty that friendly Ukrainian-Uzbek relations would develop 
further, which would also be helped by cooperation in the sphere 
of the defense complex. On behalf of the Ukrainian president, 
Defense Minister Vitaliy Radetskyy presented Defense Minister 
Rustam Akhmedov with a personal watch. 

