Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Anatoliy Ladin report: "Even Missilemen's Oath Must Be </F>
Strategic!"] 
  [Text] Tugelen Zhukeyev, Republic of Kazakhstan state 
counselor, has said that around 10,000 Kazakhstanis are serving 
in Russian troop units of the strategic forces stationed on 
Kazakhstan's territory. They have to make a choice when taking 
the military oath: As citizens of one state, should they swear 
loyalty to another? 
  Tugelen Zhukeyev believes that a special version of the CIS 
strategic nuclear forces' military oath would eliminate the 
whole thorny problem. 

