<F P=100> Kyrgyzstan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Akayev Views Economic Accord With Uzbekistan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1601185794 Moscow Mayak Radio Network in Russian 1630 GMT 
16 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1601185794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Mayak Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] An important event took place in Bishkek today. The 
presidents of Uzbekistan and Kyrgyzstan signed a number of 
documents defining the prospects for the further development of 
bilateral economic relations. Our correspondent says that the 
agreement on Kyrgyzstan joining the bilateral agreement between 
Kazakhstan and Uzbekistan on setting up a single economic space 
is the main one. Kyrgyzstan President Askar Akayev had the 
following comments: 
  [Begin Akayev recording] This is what our people, our whole 
region, needs. I think that it is a very bold step which may 
serve as the start button for getting an economic union to work 
on the scale of the whole CIS. I would like to stress once 
again that this is not a regional separation today. I think 
that this is happening thanks to decisive actions by Presidents 
Karimov and Nazarbayev. Today we formed a major economic union. 
That is, first of all, a single economic space in trade. 
Second, a single economic space envisages (?a unitarian) policy 
in the sphere of currency, in the sphere of taxation, in the 
sphere of pricing and in the sphere of investments. You can 
imagine what this means -- that now, we three states will agree 
all these questions. I think that this, to a certain extent, is 
the first historic step on the path from talks to concrete 
deeds. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-56808 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drsov014_l_94002" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-SOV-94-014 </AU>
Document Type:Daily Report 
<DATE1>  21 Jan 1994 </DATE1>

