<F P=100> Uzbekistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Khamidov Appointed To Replace Finance Minister </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1901140594 Tashkent UZBEKISTAN APN in Russian 1112 GMT 19 
Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1901140594 </F>
<F P=104>  Tashkent UZBEKISTAN APN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] President of Uzbekistan Islam Karimov has carried 
out a reshuffle in the republic's government. Erkin Bakibayev 
has been released from his post as minister of finance. 
Bakhtiyar Khamidov has been appointed deputy prime minister and 
minister of finance. It was he who directed all financial issues 
and conducted negotiations with the government of Russia on the 
entry of the republic into the ruble zone. By the same decree, 
Khamidov is released from his post of prime minister -- chairman 
of the state committee for statistical forecasting of Uzbekistan. 

</TEXT>

