<F P=100> CAUCASUS </F>
<F P=101> Armenia </F>
<H3> <TI>   New Azerbaijani Offensive Reported in Karabakh </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1901153094 Yerevan Armenia's Radio First Program Network 
in Armenian 1400 GMT 19 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1901153094 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan Armenia's Radio First Program Network 
in Armenian 1400 GMT 19 Jan 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Armenian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Following a massive artillery barrage at 0600 this 
morning, Azerbaijani troops launched an offensive all along the 
Karabakh battle front: from Omar pass in the north to Goradiz 
near the Iranian border in the south. Comparatively large 
forces have been put into action near Mardakert. There, the 
Azerbaijanis are using all types of artillery, almost 20 tanks, 
and other armored cars. 
  According to reports from the Nagorno-Karabakh Republic 
Defense Army headquarters, by noon the Karabakh subunits managed 
to contain the enemy's pressure in all directions. 
  The Karabakh fighters witnessed an hour-long clash between 
two Azerbaijani battalions at the southeastern sector of the 
front this morning. The Karabakh side still has no information 
on the reason for the internal armed clash. 
  As to the situation on Armenia's borders, the relative calm 
there for the last two days was disrupted last night. Fire was 
opened on the defensive positions around Yeraskhavan and 
Sevakavan in Araratskiy Rayon from Nakhichevan at 2125 for half 
an hour. The Armenian Defense Ministry press service reported 
that there were no casualties. Our border guards refrained from 
retaliating. 
  No serious incidents were recorded today in the border 
regions of the Republic. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

