<F P=101> Armenia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Defense Minister Denies Air Attack on Azerbaijan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1901220294 Yerevan SNARK in English 1531 GMT 19 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1901220294 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan SNARK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Yerevan, January 19 (SNARK)--Today Armenia's Defense 
Minister Serzh Sargisyan flatly refuted the information spread 
by IMA-press agency which referring to the Azerbaijani Defense 
Ministry source runs that on January 18 Armenian assault planes 
bombed the settlements of the Kazakhskiy and Kedabekskiy regions 
of Azerbaijan. 
  "Not a craft took off from airfields of Armenia even with 
training purpose that day", the defense minister told SNARK. 
Moreover, continued Sargisyan," an inspection group from Great 
Britain aiming to assess the information in the armed forces 
arrived on January 18 in Armenia and is currently inspecting 
divisions of the Armed Forces of Armenia". 
  As to Sargisyan, such news is apparently spread for the 
justification of the Azerbaijani Air Forces' recent air raids 
upon settlements of Nagorno-Karabakh. Meanwhile, the defense 
minister did not exclude the possibility of bombing Armenia, for 
such public misinformation could be used by Azerbaijan as a 
propaganda trick. 

</TEXT>

