<F P=101> Armenia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Battles Continue in Karabakh; Casualties Given </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2001201594 Yerevan Armenia's Radio First Program Network 
in Armenian 1800 GMT 20 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2001201594 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan Armenia's Radio First Program Network 
in Armenian 1800 GMT 20 Jan 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Armenian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Armenian Defense Ministry press service reported 
that peace has prevailed in Armenia's border zones since last 
night. 
  The situation remains extremely [word indistinct] in the 
Karabakh conflict zone, where the [words indistinct] are 
continuing. 
  Though not with the original fervor, the Azerbaijani Army is 
still launching incessant attacks against various sectors of the 
front. 
  Nagorno-Karabakh Republic Defense Army headquarters reports 
that the enemy's attacks were halted on every front yesterday. 
According to verified data, the enemy lost 120 soldiers killed 
and four armored cars destroyed. Four fighters were killed and 
nine were injured on the Karabakh side. 
  The Azerbaijani troops resumed their attack against 
Mardakert 
at 0700 this morning. 

</TEXT>

