<F P=100> Georgia </F>
<H3> <TI>   General Kondratyev Reported to Visit Georgia </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1901200994 Tbilisi Radio Tbilisi Network in Georgian 1610 
GMT 19 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1901200994 </F>
<F P=104>  Tbilisi Radio Tbilisi Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Georgian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] It has emerged from reliable sources that a Russian 
deputy defense minister, General Kondratyev, has recently 
visited Georgia. He said that although he is regarded as an 
enemy in Georgia, his stance is the same as that of the Russian 
president and defense minister -- the territorial integrity of 
the Republic of Georgia. As for the political status of 
so-called South Ossetia, it is an internal affair of Georgia. 
  To verify this information, we turned to Giorgiy 
Karkarashvili, defense minister of the Republic of Georgia. He 
said that he does not possess such information. As for General 
Kondratyev, nobody in Georgia regards him as an enemy, the 
minister pointed out, adding that during the first talks on the 
conflict in Abkhazia General Kondratyev had a rather objective 
and sensible stance. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-56821 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drsov014_s_94004" </HT>


