<F P=100> Georgia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Russian General Denies Troops Sent to Georgia </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1901215494 Yerevan SNARK in English 1531 GMT 19 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1901215494 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan SNARK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tbilisi, January 19 (SNARK)--The General-Major Boris 
Dzhukov, the assistant commander of the Russian troops in 
Transcaucasia, called premature the assertions that the Russian 
troops would provide with the security of the refugees, 
returning to Abkhazia. 
  "Everything will be clear only after the meeting of Boris 
Yeltsin and Eduard Shevardnadze", he has told SNARK today. As 
it has already been reported the Russia's president visit to 
Georgia is planned on the first fortnight of February. 
  The general also refuted the rumors that the Russian special 
purpose detachments would be located in the Tbilisi suburbs to 
maintain order in the cities of Georgia. Moreover, he told some 
units of the Russian troops are dislocated from Tbilisi and 
Kutaisi to Adjaria. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

