<F P=100> Georgia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Georgia, Russia Reach Agreement on Trade </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1901221294 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 2115 GMT 19 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1901221294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By GIA-TASS] </F>
  [Text] Tbilisi January 20 TASS -- Chairman of the Georgian 
parliament Eduard Shevarnadze received a delegation from Moscow 
on Wednesday which arrived to practically implement agreements 
reached between the mayor's offices of Tbilisi and Moscow at 
recent talks. 
  Under the agreement, in the first quarter of 1993, Georgia 
is 
to receive 3,000 tonnes of potatoes, 5,000 tonnes of flour, 
1,000 tonnes of sugar, butter, vegetable oil and canned food in 
exchange for Georgian tea, champagne, mineral water "Borzhomi" 
tobacco and citrus fruits. 
  The first batch of foodstuffs is expected to arrive from 
Russia in the near future. 
  The Moscow delegation is led by Vice-Premier of the Moscow 
government, Aleksey Peshkov. 

</TEXT>

