<F P=101> Estonia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Parliament Protests Statement </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1901172894 Tallinn Radio Tallinn Network in Estonian 1600 
GMT 19 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1901172894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn Radio Tallinn Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Estonian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Riigikogu [parliament] protests resolutely 
against the position taken by Russian Foreign Minister Andrey 
Kozyrev which holds that the Baltic states are within Russia's 
sphere of interest and attempts to justify the continuing 
unlawful presence of Russian military on Estonian territory. 
Such statements are in conflict with the CSCE final act of 10 
July 1992, in which Russia pledged to withdraw her troops from 
the Baltic states' territory as soon as possible. The statement 
also conflicts with interests of international security and 
peace. For this reason the regulation of all relations between 
Estonia and Russia has come to a halt. A swift and 
unconditional withdrawal of Russian troops cannot be based on 
haggling. The Riigikogu proposes to both president and 
government to protest resolutely (?against) the Russian 
Government. The statement was issued today by 30 Riigikogu 
members and handed over to the ETA [Estonian Telegraph Agency] 
by Vardo Rumessen. 

</TEXT>

