<F P=100> INTERREGIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Baltic Premiers Discuss Security, Economic Issues </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1901113594 Riga Radio Riga Network in Latvian 1000 GMT 19 
Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1901113594 </F>
<F P=104>  Riga Radio Riga Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Latvian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] [First unidentified announcer] Talks on security and 
economic problems of the Baltic states are taking place in 
Jurmala between the prime ministers and government delegations 
of the Baltic states. The delegations are discussing issues 
related to national security, power engineering, border 
protection, customs, consular relations, trade and agriculture, 
as well as social protection. 
  [Second unidentified announcer] The delegations must agree 
on 
several fundamental issues of the creation of the Council of 
Ministers of the Baltic States and information bureaus of the 
Baltic states. 
  The prime ministers of the three countries are discussing 
the 
problems of national security and power engineering. Apart from 
that, bilateral talks are scheduled between Latvian and 
Lithuanian representatives on the construction of the Liepaja 
oil terminal as well as on the Latvian-Lithuanian sea border. 
  [First announcer] As early as on 18 January, after a meeting 
with Estonian Prime Minister Mart Laar, Adolfas Slezevicius, 
head of the Lithuanian Government, stated that power engineering 
was a priority direction in cooperation between the Baltic 
states. 
  Slezevicius and Laar were mainly speaking about the 
strengthening of cooperation in the sphere of power engineering, 
as well as the increasing of power engineering autonomy and the 
possibility of importing energy resources from the West. 

</TEXT>

