<H3> <TI>   CIS, Belarus To Sign Pact on Minsk Headquarters </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1801203294 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1723 GMT 18 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1801203294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Executive Secretariat of the CIS and the 
government of Belarus are to sign an agreement formalizing the 
location of Commonwealth headquarters in Minsk, the CIS 
executive secretary said. 
  Ivan Korotchenya told INTERFAX that the Executive 
Secretariat 
and other CIS bodies were having serious problems at present. 
He said that because "the embassies of Turkey and Ukraine, the 
U.N. mission and the premises of some commercial structures are 
located in the Commonwealth building, the government and 
high-frequency communications systems in the building have been 
disconnected, which defies all logic." 
  "The government of Belarus has still not solved the 
accommodation problem for officials from Commonwealth countries. 
The Economic Court of the CIS is situated in an unsuitable 
place, too," Korotchenya said. 
  He expressed the hope that the future agreement between the 
Executive Secretariat and the Belarusian government would, among 
other things, make provisions for the construction of a CIS 
complex in Minsk. 

</TEXT>

