<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin Signs Edict on New Government Appointments </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2001135694 Moscow Mayak Radio Network in Russian 1340 GMT 
20 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2001135694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Mayak Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] We have just received the following urgent report 
from ITAR-TASS: 
  The Russian President Boris Yeltsin, has signed an edict on 
government changes. This was announced at a news conference 
today by Viktor Chernomyrdin, chairman of the Council of 
Ministers. Oleg Soskovets has been appointed first deputy prime 
minister. Anatoliy Chubays, Aleksandr Zaveryukha, and Yuriy 
Yarov have been appointed deputy prime ministers. 
  Aleksandr Shokhin becomes minister of economics. Viktor 
Khlystun will be minister of agriculture and food. Sergey 
Shakhray is to be minister of nationalities affairs and regional 
policy. Boris Fedorov was asked to head the Finance Ministry, 
but so far he has not replied, Chernomyrdin added. 
  That was an ITAR-TASS report on a news conference at which 
Chernomyrdin announced the Russian Government reshuffle. 

</TEXT>

