<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Further on Decree </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2001151294 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1440 
GMT 20 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2001151294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Gennadiy Talalayev] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 20 January -- Viktor Chernomyrdin has read 
out a decree by the President of Russia on immediate changes in 
the composition of the government which he received just before 
the end of today's hour-long press conference. The decree says: 
To appoint on the proposal of the Chairman of the government: 
  Oleg Soskovets as first deputy chairman of the government; 
  Aleksandr Zaveryukha -- deputy chairman of the government; 
  Anatoliy Chubays -- deputy chairman of the government; 
  Yuriy Yarov -- deputy chairman of the government; 
  Eduard Nechayev -- minister of health and the medical 
industry; 
  Viktor Khlystun -- minister of agriculture and food; 
  Sergey Shakhray -- minister for nationalities affairs and 
regional policy; 
  Sergey Shoygu -- minister for civil defense, emergencies 
and natural disasters; 
  Aleksandr Shokhin -- minister of economics. 
  Vladimir Shumeyko is to be released from the post of first 
deputy chairman of the government at his request in connection 
with his election to the post of chairman of the Federation 
Council. 
  To release Yegor Gaydar from the post of first deputy 
chairman of the government at his own request; 
  To release Boris Fedorov, Sergey Shakhray, and Aleksandr 
Shokhin from the posts of deputy chairman of the government in 
connection with the alteration in the structure of the 
government; 
  In connection with the alteration in the structure of the 
federal bodies of executive power, to release Vasiliy Voznyak, 
Vladimir Kuramin, Vladimir Mashchits, and Ivan Chernoyvanov from 
the posts of chairmen of state committees of the Russian 
Federation. 

</TEXT>

