<H3> <TI>   Gives Reasons for Refusing Post </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2001181194 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1741 
GMT 20 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2001181194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Igor Galkin] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 20 Jan -- Boris Fedorov said at a news 
conference this evening that he refused the post of finance 
minister which had been offered to him in Viktor Chernomyrdin's 
reorganized government. 
  Fedorov based his decision on the fact that his two 
conditions had not been met: first, that Aleksandr Zaveryukha be 
removed from the government, and second, that Viktor 
Gerashchenko be released from the post of chairman of the 
Central Bank of Russia. 
  Fedorov added that his decision was also explained by his 
"disagreement with the program planned by the government." 

</TEXT>

