<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Says Market Reforms to Continue </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2001155494 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1506 
GMT 20 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2001155494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By BUSINESS-TASS] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 20 Jan--In an interview with an ITAR-TASS 
correspondent today, Aleksandr Shokhin, whose appointment as 
Russian Federation economics minister was also announced today, 
stated his determination to continue the market reforms. 
Shokhin expressed the hope that he would have sufficient levers 
of power to continue the policies of market reform. 
  Shokhin is the fifth economics minister since Russia started 
its radical economic reforms in January 1992. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

