<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Space Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin Awards Honors to Mir Cosmonaut </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1501130094 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1118 GMT 15 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1501130094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Moscow January 15 TASS -- Vasiliy Tsibliyev has been 
awarded the honorary title of pilot-cosmonaut of the Russian 
Federation for the successful accomplishment of a space flight 
on board the orbital research complex Mir and for a high 
professionalism displayed in performance of his duties, 
according to a decree issued by President Boris Yeltsin. 
  Tsibliyev has also been awarded the title of hero of the 
Russian Federation for courage and heroism displayed during the 
flight, the decree said. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-56883 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drsov014_b_94030" </HT>


