<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Space Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Cosmonauts Conduct Medical Experiments </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1801114594 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1108 GMT 18 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1801114594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Mission Control Centre January 18 TASS -- Viktor 
Afanasyev, Yuriy Usachev and Valeriy Polyakov worked for nine 
days during a flight on board Mir space station. 
  Medical experiments held an important place in the flight 
programme this week. Their purpose was to study the adaptation 
of the human organism to orbital flight and to assess the 
effects of weightlessness on psychophysiological reactions and 
work of cosmanauts. 
  The ultrasonic method was used on Tuesday to determine the 
characteristics of the functioning of the heart and blood 
circulation in vessels of internal organs. During the day the 
physician will undergo a similar check with the use of means for 
the prevention of unfavourable effects of weightlessness on the 
human organism. 
  The flight proceeds according to schedule. All the three 
cosmonauts are in good health and feel well. 

</TEXT>

