<F P=101> Space Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Cargo Spaceship Continues Orbital Flight </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1801124694 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1132 GMT 18 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1801124694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Moscow January 18 TASS -- Tests of an automatic 
cargo spaceship "Progress M-17" continue. On August 11, 1993, 
the cargo spaceship was disconnected from the orbital complex 
"Mir" and since then it had been performing an independent space 
flight. 
  The parameters of the cargo spaceship, reported by the Space 
mission Control Centre, are as follows: 
  -- the maximum distance from the earth - 333 kilometers; 
  -- the minimum distance from the earth - 231 kilometers; 
  -- the period of revolution - 90 minutes; 
  -- inclination - 51.6 degrees 
  All systems on board are operating normally. Information 
transmitted to the earth is being processed and analysed. 
According to the ballistic provision department of the Space 
Mission Control Centre, the cargo spaceship is expected to enter 
thick layers of the atmosphere at the end of February - 
beginning of March, 1994. 

</TEXT>

