<F P=101> Space Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Military Space Forces To Launch TV Relay Satellite </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1901095994 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0804 GMT 19 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1901095994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS string correspondent Semyon Ivanov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow January 19 TASS -- Military space forces of 
Russia plan to launch the first direct television relay space 
apparatus "Gals" from the "Baykonur" (Kazakhstan) space vehicle 
launching site today. 
  Satellite "Gals", designed at the scientific production 
amalgam of applied mechanics (Krasnoyarsk-26 city), is the new 
generation of tv relay satellites. This launch will pave the 
way to the creation of a new television satellite system of five 
similar space apparatuses. 
  The satellite is equipped with a three-mast onboard relay- 
transmitter, ensuring retransmission of regional television 
programmes through small dimension 90 cm. diameter individual 
receiving antennas. The space apparatus will be put into a near 
geo-stationary orbit of 90 degrees eastern longitude 
approximately seven hours after the blast off (scheduled for 
12:53 hours Moscow time). Later it will be manouvered to a 
stationary position of 44 degrees eastern longitude, where it 
will be used for the main purpose it is meant for. 
  "Gals" will be the first automatic satellite to be launched 
by the military space forces of Russia from the Baykonur 
cosmodrome in 1994. 

</TEXT>

