<H3> <TI>   Launch Postponed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1901103094 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1010 GMT 19 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1901103094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Semen Ivanov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow January 19 TASS -- The launch of the first 
"Gals" tv relay satellite of a new generation scheduled for 
12.53 hours Moscow time on Wednesday was postponed for one day 
because of technical reasons, TASS was told at the press centre 
of Russian space forces which gave no further details. 
  The satellite was to be launched from the Baykonur 
cosmodrome 
in Kazakhstan. 

</TEXT>

