<F P=100> Moldova </F>
<H3> <TI>   Dniester Military Commander Condemns State of Emergency </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1901155294 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1245 
GMT 19 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1901155294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Valeriy Demidetskiy] </F>
  [Text] Chisinau, 19 Jan -- The authorities of the Dniester 
Republic introduced the state of economic emergency 
[chrezvychaynoye ekonomicheskoye polozheniye] "in order to 
justify repression against the people who have run out of 
patience with the corrupt and criminal leadership," Mikhail 
Bergman, military commandant of the Dniester Republic, said 
today. Together with Lieutenant-General Aleksandr Lebed, 
commander of the 14th Russian Army, he is known recently for 
having accused the leaders of the Dniester Republic of 
"untalented leadership" and for having urged citizens to demand 
their resignation. 
  Mikhail Bergman noted that the decree by Igor Smirnov, 
president of the Dniester Moldavian Republic, says nothing about 
the collapse of the economy or steps to overcome it. However, 
the population is being prohibited from holding mass 
demonstrations and the press is being instructed strictly to 
cover only government activity. Failure to implement this decree 
will result in the dismissal of heads of state enterprises and 
organizations and the immediate shutting down of private 
enterprises. 
  Mikhail Bergman also said that the leaders of the Dniester 
Republic "deliberately refused to compromise in the talks with 
Chisinau and to regulate currency circulation with other 
republics". As a result, former Soviet rubles still in 
circulation have flooded in from all over the former Soviet 
Union. Runaway inflation has brought the economy to 
catastrophe, Bergman stressed in conclusion. 

</TEXT>

