<H3> <TI>   Dniester Republic Threatens To Cut Off Gas, Power </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2001204394 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1715 GMT 20 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2001204394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Moldovan Prime Minister Andre Sangheli said at a 
news conference in Chisinau Thursday that the leaders of the 
self-proclaimed Dniester Republic are threatening to cut off the 
gas and energy supply to the western bank of the Dniester. He 
talked with the Tiraspol leaders on the telephone Thursday in an 
attempt to avoid this development. 
  He did not think that there were good reasons for cutting 
off 
the gas supply. 
  Sangheli said that Tiraspol wanted to discontinue the energy 
supplies because Moldova had not paid for them. 

</TEXT>

