<F P=100> Moldova </F>
<H3> <TI>   Dniester Republic Outlaws Moldova Elections </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1901194994 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1722 GMT 19 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1901194994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Presidium of the Supreme Soviet of the 
self-proclaimed Dniester Republic has outlawed any activity 
aimed at the organization of elections to the new parliament of 
Moldova in the Dniester Republic. 
  In accordance with the resolution adopted on Wednesday, the 
elections to the parliament of Moldova in the Dniester Republic 
have been outlawed and the persons guilty of organizing the 
election campaign will be prosecuted. 
  Observers in Tiraspol link this decision of the Dniester 
Republic parliament with the decree of the president of the 
Dniester Republic, Igor Smirnov, on the introduction of a 
"special situation" in the region. 
  Parliamentary elections in Moldova will be held on February 
27. 

</TEXT>

