<F P=100> Moldova </F>
<H3> <TI>   Dniester Residents Ask Snegur To Permit Elections </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2101074394 Chisinau BASAPRESS in English 2100 GMT 19 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2101074394 </F>
<F P=104>  Chisinau BASAPRESS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Chisinau, BASAPRESS, 19/1/1994 -- President Mircea 
Snegur met today with inhabitants of Slobozia District and 
Tiraspol who plead for Moldova's territorial integrity and 
independence, at their demand, states the presidential press 
service. The participants have asked the president to permit 
anticipate parliamentary elections in East Moldovan district, a 
week or two before February 27th. They said the population 
could be intimidated by authorities of the so-called Dniester 
Republic. Referring to the situation in Dniester, Mircea Snegur 
said the new Parliament will have the right to grant special 
juridical statute to east regions and localities mostly 
inhabited with Gagauzians. Snegur asserted that the 
declarations of Russian Minister of Foreign Affairs Kozyrev on 
the heed to defend Russians' right in ex-Soviet republics no not 
concern Moldova, where Russians have same rights as the local 
population. This fact was confirmed by representatives of 
various international organizations that examined the republic's 
legislation, states the presidential release. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

