<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Crimean Deputy Dies From Wounds in Attack </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS2101090694 Kiev Ukrayinske Radio First Program Network in 
Ukrainian 0600 GMT 21 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> WS2101090694 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev Ukrayinske Radio First Program Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Ukrainian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Two days after a bloody attack, Crimean People's 
Deputy Iskandr Mamedov has died after having not regained 
consciousness. Mamedov had been the organizer of Mikola Bahrov's 
presidential election campaign in the Crimea. 
  As we have already reported, as the result of a terrorist 
attack -- in which still-unidentified assailants opened fire on 
Mamedov's house -- 11 people, including two of Mamedov's 
children, were wounded, two people were killed, and Mamedov was 
taken to the emergency room of a local hospital in extremely 
critical condition. Surgeons removed several bullets and grenade 
fragments from his body, which he had tried to use as shield to 
protect his children. Surgeons did everything possible, but, to 
our great regret, neither two operations nor modern methods of 
treatment could bring this kind and talented man -- the father 
of seven children -- back to life. 
  Ukrainian Radio expresses its sincere sympathy to the family 
and friends of the deceased. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

