<H3> <TI>   Rukh Assails `Anti-Popular Measures' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1801193094 Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service in Ukrainian 
1600 GMT 18 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1801193094 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Ukrainian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The central leadership of the Ukrainian People's 
Movement for Perestroyka [Rukh] has described the latest 
government moves -- the cancellation of credit arrangements, 
immediate repayment to the National Bank of loans, withdrawal of 
state subsidies for food, another round of administrative price 
rises, and procrastination in index-linking wages and delay in 
paying them -- as none other than the continuation of the war 
waged by nomenklatura in power against the Ukrainian people. 
Rukh demands the removal of these faults and warns that the 
continuation by state power of anti-popular measures will 
trigger spontaneous actions of protest which for their part will 
violate civic peace and impede a possible change in political 
tack by way of free elections. 

