<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kravchuk Orders Streamlining Local Governments </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS1901211994 Kiev Ukrayinske Radio First Program Network in 
Ukrainian 2000 GMT 19 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> WS1901211994 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev Ukrayinske Radio First Program Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Ukrainian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] To improve the system of the state and executive 
branch institutions, to eliminate duplication of their 
activities, to elevate the role and responsibility of the state 
administration while implementing legal acts and carrying out 
economic reforms, and to reduce expenditures for its upkeep, the 
Ukrainian president decided the following: The Ukrainian 
Cabinet of Ministers shall examine within two weeks a list of 
ministries, state committees, and other institutions of the 
legislative and executive branches, and will submit its 
proposals regarding their reduction and the implementing of 
other kinds of structural changes. The draft state budget for 
1994 shall also reflect a reduction of expenditures for central 
and local institutions of the legislative and executive branches 
based on 30 percent cutbacks in the central administration 
personnel and 20 percent in the local administration personnel. 
The Crimean Supreme Soviet and local councils shall be advised 
to undertake relevant measures with regard to governing 
structures, the streamlining of personnel in regional and local 
self-governments and their executive committees at an arbitrary 
scale as of 1 January, 1992 [as heard]. 

</TEXT>

