<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Parliament Commission Rejects Draft Budget </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2001211794 Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service in Ukrainian 
1700 GMT 20 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2001211794 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Ukrainian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Supreme Council commission for issues of 
economic reform and national economy management did not support 
the government's draft state budget of Ukraine for 1994. This 
has been reported by the commission chairman, people's deputy 
Volodymyr Pylypchuk. According to him, the budget document, 
although submitted as a balanced one, is unrealistic both in 
practical and theoretical terms because it envisions that 73 
percent of the gross product or 91 percent of the national 
income should be distributed through the budget. Besides, the 
draft budget envisions such a tax pressure which will reduce the 
index of the producers' business activity, believes Volodymyr 
Pylypchuk. 

</TEXT>

