<F P=100> Lithuania </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kozyrev Remarks Said To Refer to `New Annexation' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  KLD1901225994 Vilnius Radio Vilnius in International Service 
in Lithuanian 2200 GMT 19 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> KLD1901225994 </F>
<F P=104>  Vilnius Radio Vilnius </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> International </F>Language: &lt;f 105&gt; Lithuanian 
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] At a news conference on 19 January, Romualdas 
Ozolas, member of the Lithuanian Seimas, commented on Russian 
Foreign Minister Kozyrev's statement on 18 January on Russia's 
policy on what Moscow refers to as the near abroad. Ozolas said 
Kozyrev's statement refers to a new annexation of the Baltic 
states. 
  Ozolas said the meeting in Moscow was attended by Russian 
ambassadors to the CIS countries and the Baltic states, as well 
as by a big group of Russian generals. It is also noteworthy, 
Ozolas said, that the meeting was held immediately after the 
visit by U.S. President Bill Clinton in Russia. According to 
Ozolas, Kozyrev has hastily distributed the keys to the solution 
of Russia's most important problems to the generals -- the keys 
to the CIS countries and the Baltic states. This is confirmed 
by Kozyrev's words that the refusal of military participation in 
those states would be the same kind of extremism kind as 
imperial suppression by tanks. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

