<H3> <TI>   Shushkevich Confirms Deployment of Troops in Minsk </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS2101120094 Minsk Radio Minsk Network in Belarusian 1100 
GMT 21 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> WS2101120094 </F>
<F P=104>  Minsk Radio Minsk Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Belarusian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Who deployed the Interior Ministry Troops on the 
streets of Minsk yesterday? Ivan Gerasyuk addressed this 
question to the Supreme Soviet chairman as he took the floor 
during the so-called miscellaneous portion of today's Supreme 
Soviet session. Stanislav Stanislavovich [Shushkevich] confirmed 
that the deployment had indeed taken place. In the vicinity of 
the Music Comedy Theater, a battalion subordinated to the 
commander of the Interior Ministry Troops was deployed with full 
combat readiness. The commander has been summoned to the 
legislature and will provide his explanations. 
  Meanwhile, People's Deputy (Verkhun) focused attention on 
changes in the tax policy and emphasized the fact that the tax 
on fuel has already increased 50 times compared to last year. 
Deputy Trusaw again addressed the issue of the eighth 
television channel. Deputy [name indistinct] expressed his 
concerns over the fate of unemployed, elderly, and invalid 
citizens. Deputy Prakapovich one more time called for the 
adoption of temporary measures to stabilize the situation in the 
agricultural sector. Deputies also addressed other important 
issues. 
  Following the miscellaneous period, it was announced that 
the 
session will be held behind closed doors. 

</TEXT>

