<F P=100> WESTERN REGION </F>
<F P=101> Belarus </F>
<H3> <TI>   Official Seeks Vote of Confidence in State Leaders </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2001202894 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1715 GMT 20 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2001202894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Aleksandr Lukashenko, head of the Belarussian 
parliamentary ad hoc commission on corruption in top echelons of 
power, called on the Supreme Soviet at its meeting behind closed 
doors in Minsk today to hold a secret vote of confidence in 
Speaker Stanislav Shushkevich, Prime Minister Vyacheslav Kebich, 
Prosecutor General Vasiliy Sholodonov, Interior Minister 
Vladimir Yegorov, and KGB Chairman Eduard Shirkovskiy. 
  Lukashenko believes that these men are to a greater or 
lesser 
degree to blame for allowing Lithuanian authorities to kidnap 
and take to Vilnius Lithuanian communist leaders Mikolas 
Burokevicius and Juozas Jermalavicius in Minsk on 15 January. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

