<H3> <TI>   People's Movement To Form `Shadow' Government </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS2001155894 Minsk RID in Russian 1240 GMT 20 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS2001155894 </F>
<F P=104>  Minsk RID </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Forecasts predicting that left-wing forces rather 
than the opposition would come forward with demands on holding 
early legislative elections are coming true. 
  According to RID sources, the People's Movement of Belarus 
[NDB] has reaffirmed its intentions to participate in early 
elections. It has also claimed that it has better chances than 
its opponents expect. 
  Moreover, in the course of preparation for its congress, due 
in February, NDB will select candidates for the Shadow 
Government of National Salvation. A recently released statement 
confirms NDB aspirations to play an important role on the 
political Olympus: "No `coalition' or `alternative' government 
will be approved without NDB's acceptance. Any new government 
is doomed to failure without our approval." 

</TEXT>

