<F P=102>  MK2101083094 Moscow NEZAVISIMAYA GAZETA in Russian 20 Jan 94 
p 1 </F>

<F P=103> MK2101083094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow NEZAVISIMAYA GAZETA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Boris Glebov report under the "In Brief" rubric: "Yeltsin </F>
Writes Letter to Kravchuk"] 
  [Text] On 11 January, Russian President B. Yeltsin 
forwarded to Ukraine President L. Kravchuk a message of a 
personal nature. It says that the assassination of Black Sea 
Fleet press center chief Lazebnikov has been received negatively 
by the Russian leadership. This has been reported by a 
confidential source from President Kravchuk's entourage, who 
stressed that the letter proposes in a rather harsh form to 
impose order in Sevastopol by joint efforts, and to decide 
finally the fate of the Black Sea Fleet in light of the 
Massandra understandings. The letter was sent bypassing the 
diplomatic channels of the Russian Federation Ministry of 
Foreign Affairs. 

