<H4>   Kiev To Be Compensated for Nuclear Charges </H4>
<F P=102> LD2001165094 Moscow Mayak Radio Network in Russian 1600 GMT 
20 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2001165094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Mayak Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Grigoriy Karasin, Russian Foreign Ministry's 
official representative, has confirmed that Moscow will provide 
Ukraine with fuel elements for the needs of atomic power 
engineering as a compensation for the nuclear charges that are 
being withdrawn. Speaking at a briefing in Moscow he added that 
the purchase by the United States of a part of the uranium 
released during the dismantling of nuclear weapons would 
contribute to solving the financial issues that emerge in this 
context. 

