<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Russia Agrees to Prolong Sanctions Against Iraq </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2001125994 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1251 GMT 20 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2001125994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS diplomatic correspondent Dmitriy Chubarov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow January 20 TASS -- Russia has joined the 
decision of the UN Security Council to prolong sanctions against 
Iraq for 60 days, but said oil embargo against it can be lifted 
in case the latter fully complies with disarmament demands of UN 
resolutions. 
  The Russian Foreign Ministry said in a statement on Thursday 
that "certain positive shifts have been registered in Iraqi 
approach to fulfilment of decisions of the UN Security Council. 
This mostly concerns disarmament aspects which is acknowledged 
by the world community and was reflected in the latest document 
of the special commission on Iraqi disarmament". 
  Russia actively supports the idea of establishing a deadline 
for Iraq before which the efficiency of the system of control 
can be proved, as well as the honesty of Iraqis in fulfilling 
their pledges. 
  "In case after the deadline expires, and it should not last 
for more than six months, it is confirmed that Iraq honestly and 
fully implements the disarmament aspects of the Security Council 
resolutions 687 and 715, Russia will be ready to consider the 
issue of lifting the oil embargo according to item 22 of 
resolution 687", the document said. 
  Russia resolutely and invariably stands for the fulfilment 
by 
Iraq of all other resolutions of the Security Council on the 
post-crisis settlemenmt in the Persian Gulf, including the 
resolution 833 on the demarcation of Iraqi-Kuwaiti border. Only 
in this case can the issue of lifting all other sanctions 
imposed by Security Council against Iraq can be raised, the 
statement said. 
  The Russian position strictly corresponds to the terms and 
criteria fixed by decisions of the UN Security Council, it added. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

