<F P=100> Tajikistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Rebel Forces Expected To Attack Russian Troops </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1901205594 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1839 GMT 19 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1901205594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Jumaboi, field commander of the Tajik Islamic 
opposition, plans an attack on a Russian border post of the 
Khorog unit, a Tajik Foreign Ministry spokesman told Interfax, 
quoting General Anatoliy Chechulin, commander of Russian border 
troops stationed in Tajikistan, as his source. 
  The goal of the attack is to provoke a confrontation between 
Russian border guards and the Badakhshan defense force. 
  According to Chechulin, most defense commanders had said 
that 
they would support the Russian border guards if they are 
attacked. 
  The border guards, local authorities, and Badakhshan defense 
commanders are taking steps to counter such activities aimed at 
destabilizing the region, the Foreign Ministry spokesman said. 

</TEXT>

