<H3> <TI>   Envoy Delivers NATO `Partnership' Application </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS2001112094 Tallinn ETA NEWS BULLETIN in English 0754 GMT 
20 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> WS2001112094 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn ETA NEWS BULLETIN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [All names as received] </F>
  [Text] Estonian Ambassador to Brussels Clyde Kull handed 
over the application for Estonia's joining the NATO "Partnership 
for Peace" cooperation programme at the NATO headquarters 
yesterday. Kull also met NATO Deputy Secretary General Gebhardt 
Von Moltke and Chief of Cabinet of Secretary General Klaus 
Scharioth. Possible NATO-Estonian Cooperation and 
Estonian-Russian relations were discussed. 

</TEXT>

