<H3> <TI>   `Real Fears' About Ukranian Nuclear Arms Voiced </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PM2001092994 Moscow Russian Television Network in Russian 
2020 GMT 18 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> PM2001092994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Russian Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report from the "Vesti" newscast] </F>
  [Text] A press conference on the military-political aspects 
of the agreement between the Russian, U.S., and Ukrainian 
presidents was held at the Defense Ministry today. Leading 
Russian nuclear disarmament specialists expressed real fears 
about the condition of the Ukrainian nuclear arsenal. The 
stockpiles are overloaded, the personnel are poorly trained, and 
proper servicing is not carried out. Given this situation, 
Russian plants are prepared to dismantle all Ukrainian warheads 
within two years. The ball is now in the Ukrainian leadership's 
court. [Video shows warships in harbor, under construction] 

</TEXT>

