<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin Telephones Kohl About Politics, Economy </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2101131594 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1224 
GMT 21 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2101131594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Moscow, 21 Jan (ITAR-TASS) -- Russian Federation 
President Boris Yeltsin held a telephone conversation today with 
FRG Federal Chancellor Helmut Kohl. 
  Both leaders exchanged views on certain topical questions 
concerning bilateral relations and world politics. Individual 
aspects of the Russian president's visit to the FRG, due in May 
this year, were discussed, along with the planned festivities 
marking the completion of the Russian troops' withdrawal from 
Germany, the press service of the president of the Russian 
Federation reports. 
  Boris Yeltsin informed Helmut Kohl about the domestic 
political situation in Russia and about the start of the Federal 
Assembly's work. 
  President Yeltsin emphasized the invariability of the 
Russian 
leadership's course toward democratic transformations in the 
country. 

</TEXT>

