<H3> <TI>   Russia To Continue Gas Deliveries to Germany </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PM2101144694 Moscow IZVESTIYA in Russian 21 Jan 94 First 
Edition p 1 </F>

<F P=103> PM2101144694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow IZVESTIYA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> ["Own information" report from "From Our Correspondents and </F>
News Agencies" column: "Russian Gas Deliveries to East Germany 
To Be Continued"] 
  [Text] The conflict between "Gazprom" and its German 
partner "Wintershall" on the one hand and the "Verbundnetz Gaz" 
joint-stock company on the other, which IZVESTIYA reported in 
its previous issue, has by all accounts been settled. 
  INTERFAX has reported that "Wintershall" and "Verbundnetz 
Gaz" reported Thursday [20 January] that they had managed to 
reach a last-minute compromise on the price of Russian gas and 
thereby avert the termination of deliveries of it to the FRG's 
eastern Laender. It was announced that this month the sides 
will sign a long-term contract for gas deliveries from Russia. 

</TEXT>

