<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Parties Release Statement on Former Yugoslavia Policy </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2101132594 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1130 GMT 21 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2101132594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Liberal Democratic Party, Agrarian Party and 
Communist Party groups in the lower house of the Russian 
parliament made public Friday [21 January] their draft statement 
on the situation in former Yugoslavia. 
  The State Duma would denounce the use of any kind of force, 
in particular imposition of no-fly zones, against former 
Yugoslav republics. 
  The draft also calls for withdrawal of all foreign military 
contingents from former Yugoslavia and for appropriate steps to 
be taken by the Russian authorities. 
  At their Wednesday meeting the Duma speaker Ivan Rybkin and 
Foreign Minister Andrey Kozyrev had agreed that the ministry [as 
received] or his deputy Vitaliy Churkin would attend the 
discussion on former Yugoslavia during the regular Friday 
"government hour." 

</TEXT>

