<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Churkin Urges Concentrating on Achieving Bosnia Settlement </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2201210194 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 2016 
GMT 22 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2201210194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS diplomatic correspondent Georgiy Shmelev] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 22 Jan -- What is important now is to focus 
attention on the main thing, namely to complete the process of a 
political settlement in Bosnia-Herzegovina. Otherwise the world 
will continue watching the tragedy unfold, said Russian Deputy 
Foreign Minister Vitaliy Churkin. 
  In an exclusive interview with an ITAR-TASS correspondent 
upon his return earlier tonight from Geneva, where another round 
of talks between the sides involved in the Bosnian conflict was 
held, Churkin said that with every unsuccessful round it is 
becoming more difficult to hope for success at the talks on a 
settlement in Bosnia-Herzegovina. 
  It was at the previous round of talks in Brussels last 
December that another opportunity to achieve accord was missed, 
Vitaliy Churkin added. At that moment the international 
community lacks determination to bring the matter to a logical 
end, and now it is lacking even more. 
  Vitaliy Churkin said the next round is scheduled to take 
place in Geneva on 10 February. That meeting will aim to 
achieve more modest tasks, and it will be attended by fewer 
participants. Representatives of the sides will gather only to 
discuss confidence measures, so it will be a meeting with 
limited goals. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

