<F P=100> UKRAINE </F>
<F P=101> International Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Ministry Communique on Visit </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2101224594 Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service in Ukrainian 
1700 GMT 21 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2101224594 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Ukrainian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Foreign Affairs Ministry of Ukraine has made 
public a joint communique on the results of the official visit 
to Ukraine by President of the Republic of Kazakhstan Nursultan 
Nazarbayev. 
  It says: During the negotiations between the presidents of 
the two friendly states, there was a profound and constructive 
exchange of opinions on a wide range of issues of bilateral 
cooperation and international issues of mutual interest. The 
sides stated the importance of the Kazakh-Ukrainian summit 
within the context of the further consolidation of the potential 
of bilateral cooperation and interaction on the international 
scene. The presidents of Kazakhstan and Ukraine expressed 
mutual understanding of the necessity of effective efforts aimed 
at consolidating the mechanism of the implementation of the 
agreements in various spheres of bilateral relations. The 
leaders of both states pointed out the urgency of diversifying 
the forms and trends of the trade and economic relations. In 
particular, issues were considered and a relevant agreement was 
signed. 
  Leonid Kravchuk and Nursultan Nazarbayev paid special 
attention to an in-depth examination of the tendencies in the 
present-day international situation and within the Commonwealth 
of Independent States. 
  On the results of an exchange of opinions on these issues 
the 
presidents signed a Declaration Contemporary World: Challenges 
and Dangers. While discussing the nuclear disarmament issues 
the president of Kazakhstan welcomed the signing of the 
trilateral statement by the presidents of Ukraine, Russia, and 
the United States of America on 14 January this year. 
  A Treaty on Friendship and Cooperation, a Consular Treaty, a 
protocol on consultations between the foreign ministries and an 
number of other important agreements were signed in the course 
of the Kazakh-Ukrainian negotiations. The sides expressed their 
certainty that the signed documents would become a reliable 
contractual and legal basis of a mutually advantageous and equal 
cooperation between Kazakhstan and Ukraine. 
  The leaders of both countries commissioned experts to 
continue work with the aim of signing a treaty on legal 
relations and legal support in civil and criminal cases and also 
agreements which would regulate the issue on the rights of 
national minorities and the problems of deported peoples. 
  President Nursultan Nazarbayev invited President Leonid 
Kravchuk to pay an official visit to Kazakhstan. The invitation 
was accepted with gratitude. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

