<H3> <TI>   Kravchuk To Maintain Constitution on Crimea </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2101132794 Kiev UNIAR in Ukrainian 2210 GMT 20 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2101132794 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UNIAR </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Ukrainian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Kiev, 20 January -- [passage omitted] Answering 
a question on whether he would use the right granted to him by 
the constitutional amendment adopted today allowing him to 
cancel acts by the Republic of the Crimea's bodies of executive 
power should they contravene Ukrainian laws and presidential 
directives, Ukrainian President Leonid Kravchuk said: If 
Crimea's bodies of power violate the constitution and laws of 
Ukraine, including the law of Ukraine on delimiting powers 
between Ukraine and the Crimea, I will undoubtedly bring all 
actions by Crimean authorities into accordance with state 
interests. 

</TEXT>

