<H3> <TI>   Combat Situation Detailed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2101145294 Yerevan SNARK in English 1044 GMT 21 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2101145294 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan SNARK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Stepanakert, January 21 (SNARK) -- January 21 
morning was characterized by relative peace at the Karabakh 
frontier. As SNARK was informed by the press-service of 
Headquarters of the Karabakh Defence Army, there was only 
positional exchange of fire in Mardakertskiy, Martuninskiy, 
Agdamskiy and Fizulinskiy regions. The most of the tension over 
the last 24 hours was in the front line part located in the 
north-west of Karabakh -- by the Omar pass, where military 
clashes took place. Today, about 11.30 a.m. several attack 
planes of the Azerbaijani Air Forces tried to violate Karabakh's 
air space. The details are being verified. 

</TEXT>

