<F P=100> CAUCASUS </F>
<F P=101> Armenia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Power Shortage Limits Yerevan to 1 Hour Per Day </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2201050894 Yerevan SNARK in English 1352 GMT 21 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2201050894 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan SNARK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Yerevan, January 21 (SNARK) -- The so called "regime 
number 8" is retained in Yerevan. It signifies that the 
population receives electricity only for an hour or 40 minutes a 
day. Samvel Mavisakalyan, the Deputy Mayor of Yerevan, has 
informed of it SNARK today. In his opinion it would be possible 
to supply people with 4 hours of electricity only if necessary 
amount of gas reach Armenia. Mavisakalyan told Yerevan receives 
the 40 per cent of all the electricity produced in Armenia. 

</TEXT>

