<F P=100> WESTERN REGION </F>
<F P=101> Belarus </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Ministry on Arrest of Lithuanians </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1901195894 Minsk Belarusian Foreign Ministry Department of 
Information in Russian 1353 GMT 19 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1901195894 </F>
<F P=104>  Minsk Belarusian Foreign Ministry Department of 
Information </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] One of the key events in the republic's political 
life over the past few days has been the arrest by officers of 
the Lithuanian security service and law enforcement agencies in 
Minsk of the leaders of the Lithuanian Communist Party, N. 
Burokevicius and J. Jermalavicius, who have been living there 
illegally. Today RESPUBLIKA and NARODNAYA GAZETA published a 
commentary from the Belarusian Internal Affairs Ministry on this 
matter. The commentary says the following: 
  "In accordance with the treaty between Belarus and Lithuania 
`On legal aid and legal relations in civil, family, and criminal 
cases' signed in October 1992 and ratified by the Belarusian 
Supreme Soviet in February 1993, the Belarusian side provided 
assistance to a group of Lithuanian law enforcement officers 
headed by a deputy procurator general in detaining citizens N. 
Burokevicius and J. Jermalavicius. Legal grounds for detaining 
and handing over other persons who are not citizens of Lithuania 
are not established, and this was stated to the Lithuanian 
procuracy. The actions by the Belarusian law enforcement 
officers correspond to the afore-mentioned treaty and to 
international legal norms." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

