<F P=106> [By GIA correspondent for TASS] </F>
  [Text] Moscow January 19 TASS -- Georgian leader Eduard 
Shevardnadze met on Wednesday with Israel's official 
governmental delegation. The delegation included officials of 
the Israeli Foreign Ministry and some economic agencies. 
  The talks concentrated on prospects for Georgian-Israeli 
relations. Participants in the meeting also discussed the 
proposed visit by Shevardnadze to Israel, during which the two 
sides are to sign a package of basic agreements to set up a 
legal framework for ties between Georgia and Israel. 

