<F P=100> Georgia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Plans Made To Bury Gamsakhurdia in Groznyy </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2201185994 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1849 GMT 22 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2201185994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Tengiz Pachkoriya] </F>
  [Text] Tbilisi January 22 TASS -- Chechen President 
Dzhokhar Dudayev said plans have been made to bury Georgian 
ex-president Zviad Gamsakhurdia in Groznyy. 
  In an exclusive interview with the World Television News 
Company obtained by ITAR-TASS by its courtesy, Dudayev said "we 
plan to bury Zviad Gamsakhurdia in Groznyy, on the square of the 
memorial complex which is being built to commemorate the 
beginning of the deportation of the Chechen people (celebrated 
in the republic annually on February 23). This will do honour 
to all Chechen people." 
  A Georgian delegation which returned to Tbilisi last night 
had held talks in Groznyy on Gamsakhurdia's re-burial. The 
delegation included relatives of the late president, scientists 
and representatives of the georgian public prosecutor's office. 
  ITAR-TASS learnt from one of the members of the delegation 
that in Groznyy Gamsakhurdia's relatives met with his wife 
Manana. 

</TEXT>

