<H3> <TI>   Armenian Units Reportedly Launch Attack </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2101155494 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1403 GMT 21 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2101155494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Armenian units launched a large scale attack in the 
north of Karabakh on the town of Ter-Ter Thursday evening, a 
spokesman for the Azeri Defense Ministry told Interfax. The 
attacking force of about 2000 troops and nearly ten tanks 
continued the attack on Friday morning. 
  According to the ministry, the Karabakh units succeeded in 
advancing several kilometers towards Ter-Ter but the offensive 
was fended off in the early hours of January 21. In some areas 
the enemy had to retreat beyond the line of departure. 
  According to Baku reports, numerous villages in the Kazakh 
and Tauz districts of Azerbaijan were shelled from Armenia. 
There were civilian casualties. 
  The Karabakh army communique has not been available to 
Interfax. 

</TEXT>

