<H3> <TI>   Interior Minister Yerin Visits Tatarstan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1901133494 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1230 GMT 19 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1901133494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Vladimir Gondusov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow January 19 TASS -- Russian Interior Minister 
Viktor Yerin today left for Kazan, the capital of Tatarstan, a 
constituent republic of the Russian Federation, to attend a 
summing up conference of local law enforcement bodies. Yerin, 
who is member of the Russian Security Council, was absent from 
today's meeting of the council. 
  In the course of the visit, the Interior Ministry's public 
relations centre reports, Yerin will meet leaders of the 
republic, will visit law enforcement establishments and units of 
interior troops, as well as local penitentiaries. 
  The minister arrived in the capital of Tatarstan on the same 
day. 

</TEXT>

