<H3> <TI>   Tatarstan To Sign Russian Accord Before Elections </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1901191794 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1526 GMT 19 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1901191794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A bilateral agreement on mutual delegating of 
authorities will be signed by Russia and Tatarstan on March 13, 
i.e. before the second round of elections to the Russian 
Federation's Federal Assembly, Tatarstan's president Mintimer 
Shaymiyev said speaking in Kazan on Tuesday. 
  Last December the elections to the Russian Federation's 
Federal Assembly did not take place in Tatarstan because of low 
turnout. 

</TEXT>

