<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Sobchak: Petersburg To Pursue Autonomous Policy </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2101192294 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 1800 GMT 
21 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2101192294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Rossii Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Anatoliy Sobchak told journalists today that St. 
Petersburg will defend its rights as a subject of the Federation 
and pursue an autonomous policy, irrespective of what is 
happening in the Russian parliament, in particular continue with 
privatization and trying attract foreign banks and investments 
into the city. 
  St. Petersburg's mayor believes that the Russian Government 
has become economically disorientated. In Sobchak's view, in 
the conditions of the market it must, in the first place, work 
on the finance-credit system and the regulation of the cost of 
goods transportation inside Russia. 

</TEXT>

