<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Komi Republic Assembly Views Draft Constitution </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2101135494 Moscow Russian Television Network in Russian 
1100 GMT 24 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2101135494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Russian Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Vesti" newscast] </F>
  [Text] A draft new constitution of the Komi republic was 
the main subject of discussion at a meeting of the parliament's 
presidium with an increased number of participants. The draft 
tries to combine in the new basic law the principles of 
territorial sovereignty on the basis of Russian federalism. The 
articles on freedoms of citizens are being amended to bring them 
in line with universally accepted norms. A program for 
implementing the law on the Komi republic's state languages 
caused debates. The majority of lawmakers regarded a list of 
posts that require the knowledge of two languages, Russian and 
Komi, as a limitation of civil rights. No agreement was reached 
on a list of the premises that should be equipped with systems 
for simultaneous translation at the expense of the budget. A 
decision was adopted on selling oil shares to people residing in 
oil-extracting regions on a preferential basis for money and 
vouchers. A strict provision on a procedure for holding 
competition for the right to use Komi natural resources was 
approved. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

