<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Draft Constitution Published </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2301072694 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0654 GMT 23 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2301072694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Viktor Makarov] </F>
  [Text] Syktyvkar, Komi Republic, January 23 TASS -- A new 
draft constitution of the Komi Republic, northern Russia, 
prepared by a special commission at the republic's Supreme 
Soviet has been published in the local press for public 
consideration. 
  All state power bodies, public associations, labor 
collectives and inividuals are invited to submit their proposals 
and amendments to the commission, the Supreme Soviet presidium 
said in an address to the republic's residents, also released by 
the media. 
  All proposals must be submitted before February 2, 1994. 
  Under the presidium's decision, the draft constitution will 
be considered at the parliament's extraordinary session 
scheduled for February 15. 
  The draft reads that the Komi Republic is a democratic legal 
state within the composition of the Russian Federation. The 
draft nominates the multinational population of the Komi 
Republic as "the bearer of the republic's sovereighnty and the 
only source of the state power" which may execute its powers 
both directly, through participation in referendums and 
elections, and indirectly, through a system of state and local 
self-rule agencies. 
  In compliance with Russia' constitution, the state system of 
power bodies in the republic includes the state council, the 
head of the republic, the constitutional court, and a court 
system. Under the draft constitution, the state council is the 
highest representative and legislative body in the republic. 
The head of the republic is a "top official who directly leads 
the cabinet of ministers, which is the republic's highest 
executive power body". 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

