<F P=101> Estonia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Withdrawal Talks With Russia Set for 1-2 Feb </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS2101122494 Tallinn BNS in English 0731 GMT 21 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS2101122494 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn BNS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tallinn, Jan 20, BNS -- The next round of 
intergovernmental talks between Estonia and Russia are to be 
held in a location near Moscow on Feb. 1-2. 
  The talks, originally scheduled for Jan. 18-19, were 
postponed at Russia's request after the Russian delegation 
leader Vasiliy Svirin was reported to have fallen ill. 
  The two parties reached agreement on the new date of the 
talks on Jan. 20, said Ago Tiiman, secretary of the Estonian 
delegation. Russia has said it will this time present a detailed 
timetable for the withdrawal of its troops from Estonia. 
  Russia in the last round of talks suggested Aug. 31, 1994, 
as 
the final deadline for the pullout. Estonia has agreed in 
principle with the deadline but says Russia still must present a 
timetable showing the terms for the withdrawal of each major 
unit. 
  The head of the Estonian delegation, Vaino Reinart, has 
earlier said the presenting of the timetable won't affect the 
final deadline. 

</TEXT>

