<H3> <TI>   Defense Minister Cited on Defense Appropriations </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PM2101113994 Moscow KRASNAYA ZVEZDA in Russian 21 Jan 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> PM2101113994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow KRASNAYA ZVEZDA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Valeriy Gromak under "News" rubric: "If We Had </F>
the Money, Would We Buy Ourselves a Defense Capability?"] 
  [Text] Vilnius -- Budget appropriations for Lithuanian 
territorial defense needs in 1994 will remain proportionally 
unchanged compared to last year, comprising 4.6 percent of the 
budget. However, the size of these appropriations has increased 
60 percent and stands at 130 million litai (approximately $33 
million). This was announced by Prime Minister Adolfas 
Slezevicius. 
  National Defense Minister Linas Linkevicius is sure that, 
despite these meager budget appropriations, the country will be 
able to establish a defense system that befits our membership of 
international security structures. 

</TEXT>

