<F P=100> Lithuania </F>
<H3> <TI>   Services Refuse To Employ Former KGB Officer </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS2401112394 Tallinn BNS in English 1255 GMT 22 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS2401112394 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn BNS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Vilnius, Jan 22, BNS -- Lithuanian national 
security institutions categorically denied press reports that 
Vytautas Karinauskas, former head of the 1st KGB department in 
Lithuania, is employed in the National Security Service [NSS]. 
  Suppositions appeared Friday [21 January] in the RESPUBLIKA 
newspaper. 
  "He is definitely not in the staff of the service," 
well-informed sources said and added that the basic principles 
of the NSS remain unchanged -- former KGB leaders cannot be 
employed in Lithuanian security. 
  Experts said, however, that Karinauskas may have been 
invited 
for consultations when certain structures of the NSS were being 
created. The 1st KGB department was engaged in espionage. 
  Experts characterize Karinauskas as a "Western-minded" 
person, who has considerable experience of work abroad and is a 
"top level professional." Experts said Lithuanian national 
security services often lack such features. 

</TEXT>

