<F P=100> Federal Assembly </F>
<H3> <TI>   Federation Council Legislation Committee Chief on New Job </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PM1901143594 Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA in Russian 19 Jan 94 
First Edition p 2 </F>

<F P=103> PM1901143594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Interview with Issa Kostoyev, chairman of the Federation </F>
Council Committee for Legislation and Judicial and Legal 
Reforms, by Yevgeniy Skukin; place and date not given: "Laws 
Must Operate With Precision"] 
  [Text] I tracked down Issa Kostoyev, newly elected 
chairman of the Federation Council Committee for Legislation and 
Judicial and Legal Reforms, who is chief of the Investigations 
Department of the General Prosecutor's Office and a state 
counsellor third class, during a break in proceedings. (For a 
while last year he was the Russian president's representative in 
the Ossetian-Ingush conflict zone.) 
  [Skukin] Do you intend to return to the Ossetian-Ingush 
problem -- this time in your new capacity? 
  [Kostoyev] It will be time to extend the president's edict 
on the state of emergency in the conflict zone in a few days' 
time, and I, as chairman of the Federation Council Committe for 
Legislation and Judicial and Legal Reforms, will insist that a 
group of deputies travel to the trouble spot first. 
  [Skukin] Issa Magametovich, what matters within your area of 
competence are truly urgent? 
  [Kostoyev] It is essential to establish which power 
structures are to deal with what. The introduction of trial by 
jury has revealed Russia's all-around lack of preparation for 
civilized legal proceedings. Our laws are often ill-drafted and 
contradictory. A huge army of investigators from the former 
Security Ministry has been jettisoned, but not every lawyer is 
capable of being an investigator. These people won't be wasted; 
they are professionals, and they are going into commercial 
structures. Investigation, however, will suffer: Only 40 
percent of crimes are being detected now. 
  [Skukin] What will you be seeking to achieve when you start 
your new job? 
  [Kotsoyev] I will be seeking firmly and persistently to 
ensure that when we draft Russian laws we include within them a 
mechanism for their implementation. Laws must operate with 
clockwork precision. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-57079 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drsov015_c_94006" </HT>


