<H3> <TI>   Calls For Pardoning Putschists </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MK1901115094 Moscow SEGODNYA in Russian 19 Jan 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> MK1901115094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow SEGODNYA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Ivan Rybkin Supports the Idea of </F>
Amnesty"] 
  [Text] State Duma Chairman Ivan Rybkin supports the idea 
of amnestying the protagonists in the 19-21 August 1991 and 
September-October 1993 events in Moscow "with the exception of 
those who have committed an obvious criminal act." Mr. Rybkin 
is convinced that "this would be a necessary prerequisite for 
civil peace and accord." 

</TEXT>

