<H3> <TI>   Duma Refuses To Discuss Freeing Rutskoy, Khasbulatov </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1801163694 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1411 GMT 18 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1801163694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [by ITAR-TASS parliamentary correspondent Ivan Novikov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow January 18 TASS -- Deputies of the Russian 
State Duma have refused to discuss the liberation of Aleksandr 
Rutskoy, Ruslan Khasbulatov and others arrested on charge of 
involvement in the Moscow October revolt. 
  The proposal put forward by Deputy Leonid Petrovskiy from 
the 
Communist Party faction was supported by 145 parliament members. 
Petrovskiy claimed their arrest and custody violates Russian 
legislation. 

</TEXT>

