<F P=100> Federal Assembly </F>
<H3> <TI>   State Duma Adopts Provision on Committee Activities </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1801194494 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1807 GMT 18 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1801194494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] On Tuesday [18 January] the State Duma adopted a 
provision on its temporary regulations regarding activity of its 
committees and commissions. 
  According to this document, the State Duma forms its 
committees "on the basis of proportional representativeness of 
deputy associations." The State Duma determines the number of 
each committee, "which should be not less than 12 and not more 
than 35 deputies." 
  The provision says that every deputy, except the chairman, 
his deputies, and leaders of deputy associations and 
deputy-members of the government, should be in one of the Duma's 
committees. 
  A committee's session is considered valid if more than half 
of the total number of its members are attending the session. 
Decisions are adopted by simple majority of votes given the 
number of deputies attending the session. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

