<F P=100> Federal Assembly </F>
<H3> <TI>   Duma To Discuss Government Activities Every Friday </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1901103294 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0808 GMT 19 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1901103294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS parliamentary correspondent Ivan Novikov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow January 19 TASS -- The Russian State Duma 
will devote one hour every Friday to discussing the activities 
of the gvernment and the Agrarian Party plans to support its 
leader and Deputy Premier Aleksandr Zaveryukha before the new 
composition of the government is announced. 
  The Duma decided on Wednesday [19 January] that it will 
devote the last hour of each Friday to discussing the work of 
the government which lawmaker Georgiy Zadonskiy said would allow 
the lower chamber to "quickly react to various decisions of 
Viktor Chernomyrdin's team". 
  The lawmakers are also going to discuss on Wednesday a 
statement of the Agrarian Party on the current situation in 
agriculture and plan to do that before a scheduled meeting of 
the president and the prime minister who are to determine the 
new composition of the government. 
  The president and the premier stumbled over the candidacy of 
Finance Minister and Marketeer Boris Fedorov who said he might 
remain in the government only in case Zaveryukha is dismissed. 
  Zaveryukha is responsible for agricultural policy in the 
government. 

</TEXT>

