<F P=100> Federal Assembly </F>
<H3> <TI>   State Duma Calls for Agro-Industrial Program in 5 Days </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1901184294 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 1600 GMT 
19 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1901184294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Rossii Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] At the initiative of the group of Agrarian Party 
deputies, the State Duma has advised the government to adopt a 
decision within the next five days on the functioning of the 
agro-industrial sector during the current year. The resolution 
was adopted by the State Duma after a second vote on this issue, 
taken after Yegor Gaydar, leader of the Russia's Choice group, 
called on his colleagues to approve the document, INTERFAX 
reports. 
  The agrarian group circulated a statement on the state of 
affairs in the agro-industrial sector. This says that the state 
still owes farmers over 1 trillion rubles for produce purchased 
from them, including over 600 billion rubles for grain. 

</TEXT>

