<F P=100> Federal Assembly </F>
<H3> <TI>   Adopts Decree on Agro-Industrial Complex </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PM2001092594 Moscow SOVETSKAYA ROSSIYA in Russian 20 Jan 94 
p 1 </F>

<F P=103> PM2001092594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow SOVETSKAYA ROSSIYA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [ITAR-TASS report: "State Duma Recommends"] </F>
  [Text] Yesterday the State Duma adopted a decree 
recommending that the government examine within five days the 
question of the conditions for the functioning of the 
agro-industrial complex in 1994 including the solution of the 
problem of financing the economy's agrarian sector. These 
measures should be implemented, the decree stresses, with a view 
to creating the necessary conditions for building up the 
production of agricultural raw material and food and ensuring 
the stabilization and steady development of the agro-industrial 
complex under market economy conditions. 
  At the same time the chamber refused even to examine the 
statement prepared by the agrarian faction containing 
subjective, arbitrary assessments of the present situation in 
the agro-industrial complex and claiming that "the state of 
collapse in agro-industrial production is the result of the 
government's incorrect policy with regard to the agrarian sector 
of the economy and the grossest errors and blunders in 
financial, investment, and credit policy." 

</TEXT>

