<F P=100> Federal Assembly </F>
<H3> <TI>   Zhirinovskiy's Faction Third in Strength in Duma </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1901095794 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0724 GMT 19 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1901095794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS parliamentary correspondent Ivan Novikov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow January 19 TASS -- The Liberal Democratic 
Party of Ultra-Nationalist Vladimir Zhirinovskiy, which won 
elections to the new Russian legislature on a party list, failed 
to enjoy the same success in one-seat constituencies and thus 
became the third strongest faction in the lower chamber, 
according to information made public in the Duma on Wednesday. 
  It registered 63 lawmakers and Sergey Churkin is the 
secretary of the faction. 
  The Russia's Choice and the faction of independent lawmakers 
overtook Zhirinovskiy. 
  The Russia's Choice has registered 76 lawmakers headed by 
Sergey Yushchenkov, while the independents united in the "New 
Regional Policy" faction with 65 seats and Gennadiy Kalistratov 
as the coordinator. 
  The Agrarian Party is the fourth in the list with 57 
lawmakers headed by Secretary Nikolay Kharitonov. 
  The Communists come fifth with 45 seats, the Party of 
Russian 
Unity and Accord has 30 lawmakers, the Yabloko Bloc of Grigory 
Yavlinsky - 27, the "Women of Russia" - 23 and the last is the 
Democratic Party with 15 seats. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>
